Name: 133. Clone Graph
Solution: Create map for new nodes, dfs or bfs every node and add neightbors to new nodes when they are in new nodes map

Name: 57. Insert Interval
Solution: Put new interval into result. Iterate over intervals, if overlaped with last result, then merge. If not overlapped, then insert either to left or right of last result

Name: 191. Number of 1 Bits
Solution: Create bit mask with 1 bit, shift it and compare with value in a cycle

Name: 213. House Robber II
Solution: Calculate dp for nums without last value and dp for nums without first value, take max of both dp

Name: 322. Coin Change
Solution: Iterate through 1 to amount, pick smallest dp for every i, where dp[i-coin] exists

Name: 91. Decode Ways
Solution: Iterate over string and calculate dp[i] which represents number of ways to decode, if current number is single digit then dp[i-1] should be considered as current number of ways, also if current and previous character is a valid number, then dp[i-2] should be added to current dp[i]

Name: 238. Product of Array Except Self
Solution: Calculate product from left to right and from right to left, the result for i will be a product of left-to-right[i-1] adn right-to-left[i+1]

Name: 300. Longest Increasing Subsequence
Solution: For each num, iterate from i + 1 until end and for each num[j] > num[i] and calculate dp[j]

Name: 15. 3Sum
Solution: Sort nums, iterate over unique nums[i] and calculate two sum for sub array starting from i+1

Name: 417. Pacific Atlantic Water Flow
Solution: Create 2 arrays for flow, start from initial points that join the ocean and do dfs in reverse-flow direction

Name: 55. Jump Game
Solution: Start from the end and track minimal reachable index of the array

Name: 252. Meeting rooms
Solution: Sort intervals by its start, iterate over intervals and merge those that intersects with last interval in the merged list

Name: 73. Set Matrix Zeroes
Solution: Iterate over matrix and set in a buffer rows and columns to set 0. On next iteration set zero to rows and columns

Name: 56. Merge Intervals
Solution: Sort intervals by its start, iterrate over the intervals and check for intersection with last interval

Name: 572. Subtree of Another Tree
Solution: Use function to compare two trees, iterate over all nodes with dfs and compare tree if root of subtree matches the node

Name: 152. Maximum Product Subarray
Solution: Track max and min value for dp, for each dp either pick a num[i] or extend an array and multiply to num[i]. Max and min dp values should be considere too

Name: 62. Unique Paths
Solution: Create a grid dp, iterate over cell and sum current dp with dp in the cell in which robot could go

Name: 207. Course Schedule
Solution: Create course to prerequisites graph, iterate over all courses and check with recursive dfs (cycle will not work) whether course prerequisites are resolvable. Track already resolved courses and visited node for one iteration.

Name: 105. Construct Binary Tree from Preorder and Inorder Traversal
Solution: Take first node in preorder traversal as a top node, find it in inorder traversal, everyting in the left is a left subtreee, evertyhing on the right is a right subtree. Recursevely create left and right subtree if there are more then 1 node respectively

Name: 338. Counting Bits
Solution: dp[i] is a nubmer of bits, dp[i] = (dp[i-prevMaxPowerOfTwo] + 1) || 1 when i is a power of two

Name: 190. Reverse Bits
Solution: Read each bit, then shift it left (31 - i) times and summ with previous result

Name: 261. Graph Valid Tree
Solution: Build a bidirectional graph with neighbouring cells. Iterate with dfs over neighbouring cells, track visited cells and previous cell in order to detect cycle. Valid tree wood be a graph without cycle and all nodes should be connected

Name: 79. Word Search
Solution: Create a list path to track the selected cellls. Find a first match and start recursive search with dfs, in the search before visiting the neightbouring cells, add current cell to the path, after neighboring cells are visited - remove cell from path
Complexity: O(m*n*4^L), where m,n size of board, L - length of word

Name: 424. Longest Repeating Character Replacement
Solution: Use frequency map to determine the most common character. Iterate over string with sliding window and move right pointer, when condition (windowLength - mostCommonCharacterCount <= k). Otherwise move left pointer.

Name: 153. Find Minimum in Rotated Sorted Array
Solution: Do binary search over array, if left pointer value less than mid pointer, then move it to mid + 1. If left pointer greater then mid then move right pointer. Keep track of left, mid and right values
Formula: if (left < mid) l = m + 1 else r = m - 1

Name: 208. Implement Trie (Prefix Tree)
Solution: Create a tree in which root is an empty node and other nodes are characters. The word is considered stored only if node has specific flag fot that

Name: 371. Sum of Two Integers
Solution: Use XOR opeeration to determine the result of summing the each of the bits of the number. If both bits a 1 or sum of bits are 1 and carry from previous sum is 1, then 1 bit should be applied to the next bit

Name: 253. Meeting Rooms II
Solution: Create arrays with start and end times and sort them. Then iterate over each time period and increment counter of simultaneous meetings if time is a start, and decrement if time is an end. Maximum value of simulataneous meetings would be the minimum number of meeting rooms requires

Name: 5. Longest Palindromic Substring
Solution: DP: Create a table dp with size n x n, where dp[i][j] indicates where s[j:i] is a palindrome, iterate over string characters and calculate dp[i][j] considering string is a palindrome when dp[i-1][j+1] is a palindrome and s[i] = s[j]; TWO POINTER: For every index in the string, check possibility to extend left and right pointer, palindromes with odd and even length should have different checks

Name: 33. Search in Rotated Sorted Array
Solution: Find min value index with binary search, then use binary search for left or right subarray to find target.

Name: 54. Spiral Matrix
Solution: Create for points left, right, top, bottom. Iterate when left <= right and top <= bottom, add 4 cycles to add values on each side

Name: 139. Word Break
Solution: Iterate over s from end, for each i calculate dp[i] which will be true if any of the word matches substring from i until i+word.length

Name: 23. Merge k Sorted Lists
Solution: Use binary heap to determine which value should be next and index of the list

Name: 647. Palindromic Substrings
Solution: Create a table dp size n x n, where dp[i][j] indicates whether s[i:j] is a palindrome. Iterate over string from bottom to top, for each i set dp[i][j] to true, when length of substring is 1, 2 and s[i] mathces s[j] or s[i] matches d[j] and dp[i+1][j-1] is a palindrome

Name: 143. Reorder List
Solution: Put nodes into LinkedList, then remove from head and tail

Name: 230. Kth Smallest Element in a BST
Solution: Using in-order traversal put all values into the list, it will result in a sorted list. Then get list[k-1]

Name: 323. Number of Connected Components in an Undirected Graph
Solution: Build bi-directional graph. Iterate over node and mark visited nodes with dfs, before start marking increment counter of componnents

Name: 268. Missing Number
Solution: If m is missing in 0..n, then the difference in sums between 0..n and sum of the numbers in the array is a target number

Name: 121. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock
Solution: Use 2 pointers to track min buy prices and max sell price only after min prices was used

Name: 19. Remove Nth Node From End of List
Solution: Count number of nodes, then calculate node index to remove and remove node on 2-nd iteration over list

Name: 200. Number of Islands
Solution: iterate over all cells in the grid, if cell is an island, remove it and all connected islands with dfs and increment number of islands

Name: 100. Same Tree
Solution: Compare recursively with dfs, first the node values then left subtree and right subtree

Name: 572. Subtree of Another Tree
Solution: Iterate with dfs over the left tree, if current node is equal to the right node, then using dfs check if subtree on the left is eqaul to the right tree

Name: 98. Validate Binary Search Tree
Solution: Iterate with dfs, for each node check whether it is in min and max values range, min and max values should be determined by the parent value and whether visited node is left or right

Name: 435. Non-overlapping Intervals
Solution: Sort intervals by their start point, iterate over the intervals if interval doesn't overlap with last interval from the result, add it to the result. If it overlaps, then leave in the result the shosrtest one and increase number of removed intervals

Name: 3. Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters
Solution: Use sliding window over the string and hashset to track already included characters, if new character is in set, then move left window to the next character after the same aleady included character and remove all characters on the left from the hashset

Name: 198. House Robber
Solution: Iterate over array and calculate dp[i], which could be either amount from previuos value dp[i-1] or sum of dp[i-2] and value from array
